Key Match Events: Billiat (23') and Takwara (65') scored for Zimbabwe, but the match ended 0-0
Pre-Game Insights: Kenya have a good record against Zimbabwe with three wins and a draw from four previous meetings
Kenya are without defeat in six of their last seven matches across all competitions
Zimbabwe were also banned by FIFA from taking part in the last AFCON qualifying campaign
Zimbabwe have won three and lost four of their seven outings so far
Post-Match Reflections: Kenya's Michael Olunga is doubtful for this one due to injury
Collins Sichenje and Ian Otieno are both guaranteed absentees for this one as the pair sustained respective injuries during a training session
Brendan Galloway has pulled out of the Zimbabwe camp and will not be able to add to his two caps after recently picking up a hamstring injury
Khama Billiat is back in contention for the away side, having sensationally announced his return to the international scene after a three-year absence due to retirement
Miscellaneous Highlights: Kenya will begin their quest to qualify for a seventh Africa Cup of Nations tournament when they welcome Zimbabwe to the Mandela National Stadium on Friday
The Harambee Stars have been drawn in Group J of the AFCON qualifiers, where they will battle it out with Namibia, Cameroon and Zimbabwe for two spots at next year's showpiece in Morocco
Zimbabwe are yet to win any of their World Cup qualifying matches and are already five points off the pace in Group C after just four rounds of matches
Others: Kenya's possible starting lineup: Matasi; Omar, Omurwa, Omija, Okumu; Muguna, Akumu, Odada; Avire, Ayunga, Omune
Zimbabwe's possible starting lineup: Arubi; Hadebe, Murwira, Takwara, Mbeba; Munetsi, Rinomhota, Hachiro, Chirewa; Kadewere, Mapfumo
